olive oil
1 packet Risoni
1 packet Green beans
1 Courgette
2 clove Garlic
1 packet Chicken Breast
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ packet Cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Plant-Based Basil Pesto
1 packet Parsley

• Half-fill a large saucepan with water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring to the boil over high heat.
• Cook risoni in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 7-8 minutes.
• Drain risoni, then return to saucepan. Set aside.

• Meanwhile, trim and halve green beans. Slice courgette into thin rounds. Finely chop garlic.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken, turning to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook chicken steaks until cooked through, 3-6 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it’s no longer pink inside.

• Wipe out and return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook green beans and courgette, tossing regularly, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add cooked risoni, cream (see ingredients), chicken-style stock powder and plant-based basil pesto to the pan. Cook, stirring until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• Slice chicken.
• Divide supergreen creamy pesto risoni between bowls.
• Top with chicken and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!